Step 1: Landing Page
The landing page should be clean and simple with a prominent "Sign Up" button. The button should be a contrasting color to make it stand out from the rest of the page. You can use a hero image or a video background to make the page more engaging.

Step 2: Sign-Up Page
The sign-up page should have a clean and simple design that matches the landing page. The page should include a form with the following fields:

Full Name
Email Address
Password
Each field should be clearly labeled and have a corresponding input box. You can use icons or illustrations to make the page more visually engaging.

Step 3: Verification Email
Once the user has submitted the form, they will be directed to a page that says their verification email has been sent. This page should be simple and include a clear call to action to check their email. You can use a confirmation message or a success icon to make the page more visually appealing.

Step 4: Verification Link
When the user clicks on the verification link in their email, they will be taken to a page that confirms their email address has been verified. This page should be clean and include a clear call to action to continue to the next step. You can use a confirmation message or a success icon to make the page more visually appealing.

Step 5: Additional Information
If you need to collect additional information from the user, such as their date of birth or location, you can include these fields on a separate page. This page should have a simple design that matches the sign-up page. You can use icons or illustrations to make the page more visually engaging.
